                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" id="actofunion_sng_1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="dis-g"><span class="wrap">(</span><span class="dtxt">in the UK</span><span class="wrap">)</span></span></span> <span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">either of two <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/act-of-parliament" title="Acts of Parliament definition"><span class="ndv">Acts of Parliament</span></a>. The first Act of Union, in 1707, officially joined England and Scotland as one <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/kingdom#kingdom_sng_1" title="kingdom definition"><span class="ndv">kingdom</span></a>, called Great Britain, ruled by the parliament in London. The second Act of Union, in 1800, added Ireland to this group of countries, which was then called the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland.</span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
